            <div class="accordion-body">
              <p>My workouts can be completed with little or no equipment. I advise as a basic start, you would benefit from an exercise mat and a set of dumbbells suited to your weight preference. If you are Beyond and have always exercised with weights then you can carry on using the same level of weights, but please be mindful to not overtrain. The level of weights you use must allow you to perform the exercise with the correct form for the duration of the workout. If you are returning to exercise after having a baby and have had your midwife or GP sign off to recommence exercising, I would suggest you start light and take your time to progress.</p>
              <p>The ideal starter kit would be:</p>
              <ul class="mb-0">
                <li>Exercise mat</li>
                <li><%= link_to "Ball", "https://amzn.to/3GeT9vh", rel: "noopener", target: "_blank" %></li>
                <li><%= link_to "1.5kg dumbbells", "https://www.physicalcompany.co.uk/neo-hex-dumbbells-pair", rel: "noopener", target: "_blank" %></li>
                <li><%= link_to "2.5kg dumbbells", "https://www.physicalcompany.co.uk/neo-hex-dumbbells-pair", rel: "noopener", target: "_blank" %></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
          <h3 class="accordion-header" id="headingBeyondSeven">
            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseBeyondSeven" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseBeyondSeven">How do I connect with other beyond women?</button>
